---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Texas Electricity Setup Guide for New Residents | Moving Checklist 2024";
const description = "Moving to Texas? Learn how to set up electricity service, choose your first provider, and understand your electricity options as a new resident.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-texas-cream to-gray-50">
    <div class="bg-texas-navy text-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Texas Electricity Guide for New Residents</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          Moving to Texas? Welcome to the nation's largest deregulated electricity market! Learn how to choose your electricity provider and set up service in your new home.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
      <div class="bg-texas-cream-200 p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-blue-200 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-4">üéØ Quick Start: Moving Checklist</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-3">Before You Move (2-3 weeks):</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm text-texas-navy space-y-1">
              <li>‚òê Research electricity providers in your area</li>
              <li>‚òê Compare rates and plan types</li>
              <li>‚òê Choose your electricity provider</li>
              <li>‚òê Schedule service connection date</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-3">After You Move (First Week):</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm text-texas-navy space-y-1">
              <li>‚òê Verify electricity service is active</li>
              <li>‚òê Set up online account with provider</li>
              <li>‚òê Understand your first bill</li>
              <li>‚òê Set contract expiration reminder</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-4">Understanding Texas Electricity Choice</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Unlike most states, Texas lets you choose your electricity provider. You have the power to select the company, rate, and plan type that best fits your needs and budget.
          </p>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <div class="text-center bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-texas-red mb-2">100+</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Electricity providers to choose from</div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-texas-red mb-2">85%</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Of Texas has electricity choice</div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-texas-red mb-2">Free</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">To switch providers anytime</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-4">Setting Up Service in Your New Home</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <div class="bg-texas-red text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">1</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Find Your Service Area</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Use your new address ZIP code to determine which utility company serves your area and which electricity providers are available.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <div class="bg-texas-red text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">2</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Choose Your Provider</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Compare rates, contract terms, and customer reviews. For new residents, we recommend starting with a 12-month fixed-rate plan.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <div class="bg-texas-red text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">3</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Schedule Connection</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Contact your chosen provider to schedule service connection for your move-in date. Service can typically be connected within 1-2 business days.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <div class="bg-texas-red text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-4 mt-1">4</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Provide Required Information</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">You'll need your new address, move-in date, Social Security Number, and possibly a security deposit.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-4">First-Time Texas Resident Tips</h2>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-700 mb-3">‚úÖ Smart Choices for Beginners</h3>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Choose a 12-month fixed-rate plan for predictable costs</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Select a provider with good customer service ratings</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Avoid variable-rate plans until you understand usage patterns</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Set up automatic payments for potential discounts</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Keep your first few bills to track usage patterns</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-700 mb-3">‚ö†Ô∏è Common New Resident Mistakes</h3>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Signing with door-to-door salespeople</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Choosing based only on the lowest advertised rate</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Not reading the Electricity Facts Label</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Forgetting to set contract expiration reminders</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Not understanding TDSP charges on bills</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-4">Special Considerations for Renters</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            As a renter in Texas, you typically choose your own electricity provider unless your landlord specifically includes utilities in the rent.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-2">üí° Renter Tips</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm text-yellow-700 space-y-1">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Check your lease to see if electricity is included</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Consider shorter contract terms (6-12 months) if unsure about staying</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Ask about early termination fee waivers for moves</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Transfer service instead of canceling when moving within Texas</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-texas-navy to-blue-800 text-white p-8 rounded-xl">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Welcome to Texas!</h2>
          <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-blue-100">Ready to choose your electricity provider? We'll help you find the perfect plan for your new home.</p>
          <a href="/electricity-plans" class="bg-texas-red text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-texas-red-600 transition-colors">
            Find Your Texas Electricity Plan
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>